26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 20, Chapter 15, Subchapter 1, is
27 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
28 20-15-103. Cognitive assessment.
29 (a) A physician or healthcare provider who is providing medical
30 treatment in this state may offer annually a cognitive assessment of a
31 patient for cognitive function, Alzheimer's disease, or dementia if the
32 patient is:
33 (1) Sixty (60) years of age or older; or
34 (2) Forty-five (45) years or older and at a higher risk for
35 Alzheimer's disease, dementia, or impaired cognitive function, including
36 without limitation having a family history of dementia, Down Syndrome,
